name: Farida Kayed, President
bio: Hey Art Sci! My name is Farida, and I am a fourth year double majoring in Pharmtox and Human Bio with a minor in Immunology. I’m excited to advocate for you, make ASSU services accessible, and empower our community. I draw/paint, play piano, basketball, volleyball, and host events. Visit my office hours at SS 1068 or reach out at president[at]assu[dot]ca or Instagram @faridakayed.

name: Layla El-Dakhakhni, Executive
bio: "I am a fourth-year Environmental Chemistry major with minors in History & Philosophy of Science and Women & Gender Studies. My passion for science and the arts drives my advocacy for students in FAS. I love writing
column7: and Palestine. I also run The Liberation Lab. Contact me at layla[at]assu[dot]ca."

name: Sandini Kodikara, Executive
bio: "I’m a 5th-year student majoring in Applied Genetics and Biotechnology with minors in English and Immunology. I’ve taken many diverse courses and activities at UofT. As Executive
column4: I want to support younger students with advice and perspectives I wish I'd had. I enjoy writing
column7: and cooking. Reach me at sandini[at]assu[dot]ca or visit office hours at SS 1068."

name: Quintina Liu, Executive
bio: "I’m a third-year student double-majoring in Political Science and Peace
column5: with a minor in Human Geography. I care deeply about inclusivity and intersectionality and will advocate for your needs. I organize student events
column7: and am a musician who gigs around Toronto. Come see me at SS 1068 or email quintina[at]assu[dot]."
